Smart Agent Ledger is designed for local-first AI agent usage observability.
It reads local usage logs, local databases, and optional trusted team-node
collector endpoints. Do not publish real API keys, machine names, private IPs,
ledger exports, customer data, or local log files in issues, examples, docs,
or pull requests.

Third-party names such as Codex, Claude Code, Cursor, Trae, Hermes, OpenClaw,
LiteLLM, FastAPI, uvicorn, httpx, Feishu, and Lark belong to their respective
owners. They are referenced only to describe compatibility or integration
surfaces.
